  "text": "Full-length DUX4 transcripts (DUX4fl) encode the complete DUX4 protein. The introns in the 3′ UTR are alternatively spliced to generate two DUX4fl transcripts [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . A further alternative transcript uses a splice donor site within the coding region. If translated, this splice form (DUX4s) would encode a protein retaining the homeodomains but lacking the C-terminal 264 amino acid transactivation domain.",
